{"title_page": "List of Alaska state prisons", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:SpringCreekEntrance.jpg|thumb|[[Spring Creek Correctional Center]] in [[Seward, Alaska]].]]\n\nThe '''state prison system in Alaska''', comprising both pre-trial booking and long-term incarceration for sentenced prisoners, is a unified system run by the [[Alaska Department of Corrections]].  Prior to the establishment of the department during the early 1980s, corrections was a division of the [[Alaska Department of Health and Social Services]].  That department still operates juvenile correctional facilities through its [[Alaska Division of Juvenile Justice|Division of Juvenile Justice]].{{citation needed|date=December 2015}}\n\nThere are no [[List of U.S. federal prisons|federal prisons]] located in the state of Alaska.  Federal prisoners awaiting trial or sentencing are typically held in state facilities.  Prisoners who have been sentenced are usually sent to [[Federal Correctional Institution, Sheridan|FCI Sheridan]], located in [[Sheridan, Oregon]], to serve their sentences.{{citation needed|date=December 2015}}\n\n== Facilities ==\n\n[[List of U.S. state prisons|State prisons]] in [[Alaska]] are as follows:\n\n=== Facilities ===\n\n* Anchorage Correctional Complex, [[Anchorage, Alaska|Anchorage]] (working capacity 850), including:  \n** Anchorage Correctional Complex East, formerly known as Anchorage Jail\n** Anchorage Correctional Complex West, formerly known as Cook Inlet Pre-Trial\n* Anvil Mountain Correctional Center, [[Nome, Alaska|Nome]] (capacity 115)\n* Fairbanks Correctional Center, [[Fairbanks, Alaska|Fairbanks]] (capacity 257)\n* [[Goose Creek Correctional Center]], [[Point MacKenzie, Alaska|Point MacKenzie]], between Anchorage and [[Wasilla, Alaska|Wasilla]] (capacity 1,536) Medium Security\n* Hiland Mountain Correctional Center, Anchorage ([[Eagle River, Alaska|Eagle River]]) (capacity 415), the state's dedicated facility for female prisoners<ref>\"[http://www.correct.state.ak.us/institutions/hiland-mountain Hiland Mountain Correctional Center]\" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6dkEY0x1L Archive]). [[Alaska Department of Corrections]]. Retrieved on December 13, 2015.</ref>\n* Ketchikan Correctional Center, [[Ketchikan, Alaska|Ketchikan]] (capacity 71)\n* Lemon Creek Correctional Center, [[Juneau, Alaska|Juneau]] (capacity 248), both intake facility and prison<ref>\"[http://www.correct.state.ak.us/institutions/lemon-creek Lemon Creek Correctional Center]\" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6dkEiXPac Archive]). [[Alaska Department of Corrections]]. Retrieved on December 13, 2015.</ref>\n* Mat-Su Pretrial Facility, [[Palmer, Alaska|Palmer]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.latimes.com/politics/la-na-alaska-palin-20171218-story.html |newspaper=[[The Los Angeles Times]] |title=Track Palin called cops 'peasants,' asked father to shoot him, court documents say |first=Seema |last=Mehta |date=December 18, 2017}}</ref> (capacity 112)\n* Palmer Medium and Minimum Correctional Centers, [[Palmer, Alaska|Palmer]] (capacity 492) Scheduled for closing - Located in Sutton\n* [[Spring Creek Correctional Center]], [[Seward, Alaska|Seward]](capacity 535) Maximum Security. \n* [[Wildwood Correctional Complex|Wildwood Correctional Center]], near [[Kenai, Alaska|Kenai]](capacity 255) Medium Security.\n* [[Wildwood Correctional Complex|Wildwood Pretrial Facility]], near [[Kenai, Alaska|Kenai]](capacity 113) All custody.\n* Yukon-Kuskokwim Correctional Center, [[Bethel, Alaska|Bethel]] (capacity 207)\n* Point MacKenzie Correctional Farm, [[Point MacKenzie, Alaska|Point MacKenzie]](closed 2014)\n\n<!--Don't forget defunct facilities, how or if Barrow and Kotzebue jails relate to state corrections, etc.  Halfway houses, maybe?-->\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Alaska}}\n* [[List of law enforcement agencies in Alaska]]\n* [[List of United States state correction agencies]]\n* [[List of U.S. state prisons]]\n* [[Prison]]\n{{-}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.correct.state.ak.us Alaska Department of Corrections]\n\n[[Category:Lists of buildings and structures in Alaska|Prisons]]\n[[Category:Lists of United States state prisons|Alaska]]\n[[Category:Prisons in Alaska| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[File:SpringCreekEntrance.jpg|thumb|[[Spring Creek Correctional Center]] in [[Seward, Alaska]].]]\n\nThe '''state prison system in Alaska''', comprising both pre-trial booking and long-term incarceration for sentenced prisoners, is a unified system run by the [[Alaska Department of Corrections]].  Prior to the establishment of the department during the early 1980s, corrections was a division of the [[Alaska Department of Health and Social Services]].  That department still operates juvenile correctional facilities through its [[Alaska Division of Juvenile Justice|Division of Juvenile Justice]].{{citation needed|date=December 2015}}\n\nThere are no [[List of U.S. federal prisons|federal prisons]] located in the state of Alaska.  Federal prisoners awaiting trial or sentencing are typically held in state facilities.  Prisoners who have been sentenced are usually sent to [[Federal Correctional Institution, Sheridan|FCI Sheridan]], located in [[Sheridan, Oregon]], to serve their sentences.{{citation needed|date=December 2015}}\n\n== Facilities ==\n\n[[List of U.S. state prisons|State prisons]] in [[Alaska]] are as follows:\n\n=== Facilities ===\n\n* Anchorage Correctional Complex, [[Anchorage, Alaska|Anchorage]] (working capacity 850), including:  \n** Anchorage Correctional Complex East, formerly known as Anchorage Jail\n** Anchorage Correctional Complex West, formerly known as Cook Inlet Pre-Trial\n* Anvil Mountain Correctional Center, [[Nome, Alaska|Nome]] (capacity 115)\n* Fairbanks Correctional Center, [[Fairbanks, Alaska|Fairbanks]] (capacity 257)\n* [[Goose Creek Correctional Center]], [[Point MacKenzie, Alaska|Point MacKenzie]], betw